Questions:
Which of the following is an experimental procedure being tested in the research study for breast cancer survivors with lymphedema?
A) Standard therapy sessions twice per week for 8 weeks;
B) Use of a compression garment to manage arm swelling;
C) Specific exercises aimed at improving hand mobility and grip strength;
D) Manual Lymphatic Drainage and compression applied to the swollen arm.

Correct answer: C

If you decide not to participate in the hand mobility and grip strengthening exercise study, what is an alternative treatment option for managing lymphedema after breast cancer treatment?
A) You may continue with the usual care for your swollen arm;
B) You will be required to participate in a different research study;
C) There are no alternative treatments available outside the study;
D) You will be provided with a new experimental drug therapy.

Correct answer: A

If you experience an injury as a result of participating in the study, where can you seek medical care?

A) Only at the clinic where the study is conducted;
B) At any hospital of your choice, and the care may be billed to you or your insurance;
C) The study will provide free medical services for any injuries;
D) Medical care is not available for injuries related to the study.

Correct answer: B) At any hospital of your choice, and the care may be billed to you or your insurance;
